00:34:37.520 --> 00:34:45.849
going to do tomorrow. The problem is, anything
that you might tell me or I might learn or

00:34:45.849 --> 00:34:54.790
read about, or anything that happens in society,
I can't really use.

00:34:54.790 --> 00:35:07.760
I have to put it aside because I'm locked
into some other novel altogether. And sometimes

00:35:07.760 --> 00:35:12.810
it might be an historical novel even. The
joy of the short story is anything that you

00:35:12.810 --> 00:35:22.910
want to address, you can address over a period
of six to eight months or however long I might

00:35:22.910 --> 00:35:28.039
be writing stories. The downside is in-between
stories, you are bereft.

00:35:28.039 --> 00:35:34.559
You have nothing to do. You're completely
nuts. You realize that you're doomed. You're

00:35:34.559 --> 00:35:40.609
a failure. You've never written anything before.
You'll never write anything again. You're

00:35:40.609 --> 00:35:46.930
over the hill. And you only think about a
suicide for the first week.

00:35:46.930 --> 00:35:51.119
Then, maybe, a glimmer of a story comes and
you start with a sentence. I always see something

00:35:51.119 --> 00:35:58.420
and then I start with a sentence and then
I try to follow that. I might, the first couple

00:35:58.420 --> 00:36:05.609
of days I might just get one paragraph done.
Once you get into the flow and your unconscious

00:36:05.609 --> 00:36:10.650
mind takes over, then the story reveals itself.
You find the ending. It might take another

00:36:10.650 --> 00:36:16.140
two weeks. Then you have the dead week at
the end where you're trying to figure out

00:36:16.140 --> 00:36:24.170
what you're going to do with your life. And
this is of course why all writers are drug

00:36:24.170 --> 00:36:30.410
addicts and alcoholics, and why they beat
their wives, their children and their dogs.

00:36:30.410 --> 00:36:32.809
Except for me. I'm exceptional.

00:36:32.809 --> 00:36:33.869
[pause]

00:36:33.869 --> 00:36:34.930
Yes.

